description: MACConfiguration:  Table storing MAC layer configuration parameters for various cells at specific times and locations.  `dateTime`: Timestamp of configuration; `Area_Name`: Geographic area of the cell; `CellId`: Unique identifier of the cell; `Id2`: Redundant cell identifier; `Id3`:  Default identifier; `Id4`:  Default identifier; `vsDataType`: Data type identifier; `vsDataFormatVersion`: Version of data format; `MACConfiguration.ulMaxHARQTx`: Maximum HARQ transmissions for uplink; `MACConfiguration.dlMaxHARQTx`: Maximum HARQ transmissions for downlink; `MACConfiguration.ulTtiBundlingMaxHARQTx`: Maximum HARQ transmissions for uplink with TTI bundling; `MACConfiguration.dlMaxHARQMsg4Tx`: Maximum HARQ messages for downlink; `MACConfiguration.mACConfigurationId`: Internal ID of the configuration.
